  "prompt": "What is the most abundant rock on earth?",
  "response": "The most abundant rock on Earth is basalt. It primarily makes up the oceanic crust and is formed from the rapid cooling of basaltic lava. Basalt is dense, fine-grained, and rich in iron and magnesium, making it a key component of the Earth's crust. In contrast, granite is the most abundant intrusive igneous rock found in continental crust, but in terms of overall abundance on the planet, basalt takes the lead.",
